51.1	Flash_(Barry_Allen)	Flash (Barry Allen)	The Flash is a fictional character, a superhero in the DC Comics universe. He is the second character known as the Flash. The character first appeared in Showcase #4 (Oct. 1956), created by writers Robert Kanigher and John Broome and penciler Carmine Infantino. His name combines talk show hosts Barry Gray and Steve Allen. His death in 1985 removed the character from the regular DC lineup for 23 years. His return to regular comics occurred in 2008 within the pages of Grant Morrison's Final Crisis limited series.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/a/a6/Barryallen-kitson.JPG/236px-Barryallen-kitson.JPG
